**Microsoft Learn** is Microsoft’s **free**, official, interactive learning platform where you can:

- Learn Azure, Microsoft 365, Power Platform, AI, GitHub, Windows, .NET, SQL, Dynamics 365, Security + more
- Do **real hands-on labs** in your browser (no credit card needed for most modules)
- Earn **badges**, **trophies**, and **certifications**
- Prepare for official Microsoft exams (many paths give 50–100% discount vouchers)

This README is your personal **learning map** — beginner to expert — updated for 2025–2026 trends.

---

## 🎯 Why Microsoft Learn in 2025–2026?

- AI is everywhere → Copilot, Azure AI, Fabric, Phi-3/4 models, Azure OpenAI
- Cloud is still growing fast → most in-demand jobs require Azure
- Low-code / No-code explosion → Power Apps, Power Automate, Power BI
- Huge demand for security & compliance skills
- Free forever (no subscription required)

---

## 🚀 Learning Paths by Skill Level

### 🟢 Level 1 – Absolute Beginner (0–3 months)

Goal: Understand what Microsoft offers and get your first badge

Recommended starting paths (in this order):

1. **[Welcome to Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/get-started-with-microsoft-learn/)**  
   → Create account, understand badges, leaderboards, profiles

2. **[Azure Fundamentals AZ-900](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/azure-fundamentals-describe-cloud-concepts/)**  
   → Cloud basics, what is Azure, IaaS/PaaS/SaaS, pricing, support

3. **[Microsoft 365 Fundamentals MS-900](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/microsoft-365-fundamentals/)**  
   → Teams, Outlook, OneDrive, SharePoint, security basics

4. **[Power Platform Fundamentals PL-900](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/power-platform-fundamentals/)**  
   → What is low-code? Power Apps, Power Automate, Power BI, Dataverse

5. **[Introduction to Generative AI](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/introduction-generative-ai/)**  
   → Very important in 2025–2026!

**Milestone badges to collect first:**
- Azure Fundamentals
- Microsoft 365 Fundamentals
- Power Platform Fundamentals
- AI-900: Azure AI Fundamentals (very popular)

---

### 🟡 Level 2 – Beginner to Intermediate (3–9 months)

Goal: Build real projects and decide your specialization

Popular specializations:

**Cloud / Azure**
- AZ-104: Azure Administrator
- AZ-204: Developing Solutions for Azure
- AZ-305: Designing Microsoft Azure Infrastructure Solutions

**Data & AI**
- DP-203: Data Engineering on Microsoft Fabric & Azure
- DP-600: Fabric Analytics Engineer
- AI-102: Designing and Implementing a Microsoft Azure AI Solution

**Low-Code / Business Apps**
- PL-100: Microsoft Power Platform App Maker
- PL-200: Microsoft Power Platform Functional Consultant
- PL-400: Microsoft Power Platform Developer

**Security**
- SC-900: Microsoft Security, Compliance, and Identity Fundamentals
- SC-200: Microsoft Security Operations Analyst

**Developer**
- AZ-204 → then either .NET, GitHub Actions, or Azure Functions

**Recommended order for most people in 2025:**
1. AZ-900 + AI-900 + PL-900
2. Pick one role: Administrator (AZ-104), Developer (AZ-204), Data (DP-203/DP-600), Security (SC-200), Power Platform (PL-200/PL-400)

---

### 🔴 Level 3 – Advanced / Expert (9+ months)

Goal: Become job-ready or go for Architect / Specialty level

**Most respected advanced certifications (2025–2026):**

- **AZ-305** – Designing Azure Infrastructure Solutions (Architect)
- **DP-600** – Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate
- **AI-102** – Azure AI Engineer Associate
- **AZ-400** – DevOps Engineer Expert
- **SC-100** – Cybersecurity Architect Expert
- **DP-500** – Designing and Implementing Enterprise-Scale Analytics Solutions (very hot)

**Expert-level paths people aim for:**
- Solutions Architect Expert → AZ-305 + AZ-104 + AZ-204
- DevOps Engineer Expert → AZ-400 + AZ-204 + AZ-104
- Data Engineer → DP-203 + DP-600 + DP-500

---

## 🛠️ Best Learning Strategy (2025–2026)

1. **Daily habit** → 30–60 min every day
2. **Always do the hands-on labs** — theory alone is not enough
3. **Use Sandbox** when available (free temporary Azure environment)
4. **Join Microsoft Learn community** → ask questions, help others
5. **Track progress** → https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/profile/
6. **Collect vouchers** → many modules give 50–100% off exam fee
7. **Schedule exam** → Pearson VUE or online proctored

